07e7745a-c195-4f9a-94b9-7839068a5caf.46d8d905-2dbd-4191-8e4d-66d88d41f7c0.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null. 
Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - if the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - if some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
07e7745a-c195-4f9a-94b9-7839068a5caf.95a52b67-9282-424b-95af-efcc33cf5419.prompt=${CSA_SiteScope_RootMonitorGroup}\${reqOrgName}\${reqUserName}\${SVC_INSTANCE_ID}\${hostname} 07e7745a-c195-4f9a-94b9-7839068a5caf.9de74879-6c62-4328-8cd7-a62a5055760d.description=
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.
07e7745a-c195-4f9a-94b9-7839068a5caf.description=
This flow runs Create Server Monitor action for created target VM on sitescope server. This flow creates a monitor entry for target VM in sitescope server. CSA templates must be deployed and available in sitescope server before invoking this flow.

Inputs\:
serverIPAddress	\: The IP address of the provisioned vm
serverId		\: The server component Id
serverHostname	\: The host name of the provisioned vm
sisTemplatePath	\: The path of deployed csa template in your sitescope host (e.g \: CSA templates\LINUX)
monitorHost		\: The DNS name or IP address of your SiteScope host.
monitorPort 		\: The port to connect to your SiteScope host on.
monitorProtocol	\: The protocol to connect to your SiteScope host with (HTTP or HTTPS).  HTTPS is not configured by default during SiteScope install.
monitorUser		\: The username for the SiteScope host.
moitorPassword 	\: The password for the SiteScope user.
monitorPath		\: The complete monitor path to be created in sitescope server 
		  (e.g \: CSA Monitors\${reqOrgName}-${reqUserName}\${SVC_INSTANCE_ID}${hostname})
   

Response\:
success		\: Server monitor creation succeeded for the target VM in sitescope server
failure		\: Server monitor creation failed for the target VM in sitescope server
07e7745a-c195-4f9a-94b9-7839068a5caf.ee3fd2f8-f077-42d7-9a5d-295caf7801cd.prompt=Target host name\: 07e7745a-c195-4f9a-94b9-7839068a5caf.f0b28ab1-0e74-4526-9a48-ecc825ee625e.description=
Runs a Ping command either locally or remotely depending on the specified protocol. Credentials and other inputs (remoteOS, hostname, username, password, keyFile etc) are required if the command must be run from a remote host. The Telnet protocol also requires inputs for usernamePrompt and passwordPrompt. 

Inputs\:
hostname 		- Hostname or IP address of the host computer where the Ping command will be executed.
username 		- A username to authenticate to the host computer. 
password 		- The password for the user account.
targetHost 		- Hostname or IP address of the target host computer.
protocol 		- The protocol used to run the command (ssh, Telnet or local only are supported)
packetSize 		- The size of the ping packet.
packetCount 	- The number of ping packets to send.
remoteOS 		- The operating system of the host computer (WINDOWS, LINUX, SOLARIS only are supported), if Ping is running on a remote host.
usernamePrompt	- The username prompt seen while using Telnet protocol. This input is required when Telnet protocol is used. For example, login\:.
passwordPrompt 	- The password prompt seen while using Telnet protocol. This input is required when Telnet protocol is used. For example, password\:.
keyFile 		- The path to the private key file for remote host. The path should be relative to the ICONCLUDE_HOME environmrnt variable.
timeout                               - The timeout in miliseconds for the Ping operation. Default is 90000.

Responses\:
success 		- The command executed successfully.
failure 		- The command could not be executed or had a problem during execution.

Returns\:
packetsSent 		- The number of packets sent.
packetsReceived 	- The number of packets received.
percentagePacketsLost 	- The percentage of packets lost.
transmissionTimeMin 	- Minimum time taken for transmitting the packet.
transmissionTimeMax 	- Maximum time taken for transmitting the packet.
transmissionTimeAvg 	- Average time taken for transmitting the packet.
returnResult 		- Raw output of the command.
returnCode 		- Return code of the executed command.
error 		- The STDERR of the command.
